{
  "answer": "The sought-after couplet (the *matla* or opening *sher* of the ghazal) by Mirza Ghalib is found in his *Diwan-E-Ghalib*.[^1]\n\n**Original (Urdu, Perso-Arabic script):**  \nبازیچۂ_اطفال ہے دنیا مرے آگے  \nہوتا ہے شب_و_روز تماشا مرے آگے[^2]\n\n**Transliteration:**  \nbaazeecha-e-atfaal hai duniya mere aage  \nhota hai shab-o-roz tamasha mere aage[^3]\n\n**Translation:**  \nThis world is but a children's game, a vast display,  \nWhere night and day a spectacle unfolds my way.[^4]\n\nThis ghazal (ch. 213) philosophically elaborates on the world as mere play (*baazeecha-e-atfaal*) and spectacle (*tamasha*) before the poet's transcendent gaze.[^5]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 213 (\"baazeecha-e-atfaal hai duniya mere aage\"), [translation](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/213-baazeecha-e-atfaal-hai-duniya-mere-aage/translation/).\n\n[^2]: *Ibid.*, [original](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/213-baazeecha-e-atfaal-hai-duniya-mere-aage/original/#p-cb8975).\n\n[^3]: *Ibid.*, [transliteration](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/213-baazeecha-e-atfaal-hai-duniya-mere-aage/transliteration/#p-6c6c39) (opening lines).\n\n[^4]: *Ibid.*, [translation](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/213-baazeecha-e-atfaal-hai-duniya-mere-aage/translation/#p-3132be).\n\n[^5]: *Ibid.*, [translation](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/213-baazeecha-e-atfaal-hai-duniya-mere-aage/translation/).",
